<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,1400]" pageId="15" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,269,439,464]" pageId="15" pageNumber="56">Head.</emphasis>
Clypeus broad, semi–circular, bordered by two teeth on anterior edge which are wider than longer. Genae right angled. Frontoclypeal suture clearly evident slightly curved without tubercle in the middle. Frons densely punctate with small round punctures. Clypeogenal suture present but poorly defined towards the clypeal edge. Clypeus densely punctate with fine punctures becoming rugose towards the clypeal frontal margin.
</paragraph>
